:R-HSA-1483152  a           obo:GO_0006644 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Lysophosphatidylethanolamine (LPE) is hydrolyzed by phospholipases to produce glycerophosphoethanolamine (GPETA) which is in turn hydrolyzed by glycerophosphocholine phosphodiesterase to produce ethanolamine (ETA) and glycerol-3-phosphate (G3P) (Yamashita et al. 2009, Yamashita et al. 2005)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Hydrolysis of LPE" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Williams, MG, 2011-08-12" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Wakelam, Michael, 2012-05-14" , "Authored: Williams, MG, 2011-09-14" ;
